        {
          "id": "f7a8eeb0-5df0-4a5a-a33e-1519fd3c9646",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "body",
          "html": "<div><br></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><br></b></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><br></b></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Weighted undirected graphs, Laplacians, Random Walks</div><div style=\"text-align: center;\">are all basically the same concept</div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\">if we make the graph directed,&nbsp;</div><div style=\"text-align: center;\">then all of this equivalence breaks down</div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br></div>",
