        {
          "id": "52bdd193-7a10-4a99-84ed-db4a5e1b6524",
          "type": "text",
          "preset": "body",
          "html": "<div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>Drop direction entirely [ ??? ]</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>$$\\mG \\to \\mA = \\max(\\mG, \\mG^T)$$</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i><br></i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>Explicitly symmetrize the matrix [ ??? ]&nbsp;</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>$$\\mG \\to \\mA = \\mG + \\mG^T$$</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i><br></i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>Use singular values instead of eigenvalues [Dhillon ’??, probably even earlier]</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>$$\\mG \\to \\mA = \\bmat{0 &amp; \\mG \\\\ \\mG^T &amp; 0}$$</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i><br></i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>Use directed graph directly [ … many attempts … ]&nbsp;</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>$\\mG \\to \\mA = \\mG \\mD^{-1}$ and things like hitting tims, etc.&nbsp;</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i><br></i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\"><i>Flow-based circulation [Chung 2005]</i></div><div style=\"font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\">$\\mG \\to \\mA = \\text{Diag}(\\vpi(\\mG)) \\mD^{-1} \\mG + \\mG^T \\mD^{-1} \\text{Diag}(\\vpi(\\mG)) \\mG^T$</div>",
          "position": {
            "x": 68,
            "y": 241,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 800
          }
        }
